Estonian Teachers Demand 20% Pay Rise From 2012, Paeevaleht Says

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-04-25T07:37:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/estonian-teachers-demand-20-pay-rise-from-2012-paeevaleht-says.html
Estonian teachers want a 20 percent
pay increase from next year,  Eesti Paeevaleht  reported, citing
Sven Rondik, chairman of the education workers’ union.  The union wants the starting gross monthly wages for
teachers to rise to 729 euros ($1,062) from 608 euros now, the
Tallinn-based newspaper reported  Rondik as saying. Teachers
with the highest qualification would receive 1,066 euros,
compared with 888 euros. The union also wants increases in
junior teachers’ pay over the next three years to bring it in
line with average nationwide wage of 900 euros by 2014, as
forecast by the  Finance Ministry , the paper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
